.TH BROKER-SERVICE 8 "@man_date@" "Broker Service @version@" "System Manager's Manual"
.SH NAME
broker-service \- A service that acts as a message broker for PUB-SUB patterns.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B broker-service
[\fB--verbose\fR] [\fB--help\fR] [\fB--version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBbroker-service\fR is a command-line tool that starts a message broker, which facilitates communication between publishers and subscribers using the ZeroMQ library.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--verbose\fR
Enable verbose output, providing more detailed logs about the broker's operation.
.TP
\fB--help\fR
Display help information about the \fBbroker-service\fR command.
.TP
\fB--version\fR
Display the version of the \fBbroker-service\fR.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start the broker service with verbose output:
.nf
\fBbroker-service --verbose\fR
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
\fBzeromq\fR(7).

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Martin Lund

